trees.work_to_be_performed: Prune and remove all dead, dying, diseased, interfering, objectionable weakly attached low vigor branches 1" in diameter. Dead wood greater than 2' in length to be removed regardless of diameter.

Prune and remove all dead, dying, diseased, interfering, objectionable weakly attached low vigor branches 1" in diameter. Dead wood greater than 2' in length to be removed regardless of diameter. Inspect, raise and fix lighting protection as needed, as of 2020 the highest terminal was 13-15' below branch tip heights. Inspect all current cabling systems. New cabling will need to be installed higher and farther out to compensate for past growth. Two large limbs on the South and Southwest side of the tree will need at least one new cable each. Total amount of cabling is approximately 50-75 yards in length.
